    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1900-08-07T23:59:59-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1900-08-07T00:00:00-05:00" n="370"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d370">
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">Mr. <persName type="from">Porter</persName> to Mr. <persName
                            type="to">Hay</persName>.</hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Embassy of the United States</hi>,<lb/>
                            <hi rend="italic">Paris</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1900-08-07">
                            <hi rend="italic">August 7, 1900</hi>
                        </date>.</dateline>
                    <seg rendition="#left">No. 711.]</seg>
                </opener>
                <p>
                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Sir</hi>: Your cable received on the 2d instant,<note n="2"
                        xml:id="d370fn2">Printed ante.</note> transmitting the substance of the
                    suggestion made by Li Hung Chang, was communicated to the minister of foreign
                    affairs, who acknowledged receipt of this information by a short note, copy
                    herewith inclosed.</p>
                <p>I have the honor to be, etc.,</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Horace Porter.</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
                <frus:attachment>
                    <opener>
                        <seg rendition="#center">[Inclosure—Translation.]</seg>
                    </opener>
                    <head>
                        <hi rend="italic">Mr. <persName type="from">Delcassé</persName> to Mr.
                                <persName type="to">Vignaud</persName>.</hi>
                    </head>
                    <opener>
                        <dateline rendition="#right">
                            <placeName>
                                <hi rend="smallcaps">Paris</hi>
                            </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1900-08-04">
                                <hi rend="italic">August 4, 1900</hi>
                            </date>.</dateline>
                    </opener>
                    <p>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Mr. Charge d’affaires</hi>: You have been kind enough
                        to communicate to me, under date of yesterday, the contents of a telegram
                        which you have received from the Federal secretary of state for foreign
                        affairs, which treats of an exchange of communications <pb facs="0414"
                            n="316" xml:id="pg_316"/> between your Government and the viceroy of the
                        two Kuang, relative to the situation of the foreign representatives at
                        Pekin.</p>
                    <p>In thanking you for having transmitted to me this document, I am pleased to
                        testify to the commonality of views existing between the Government of the
                        United States and that of the French Republic.</p>
                    <p>Accept, Mr. Chargé d’Affaires, the assurance of my highest consideration.</p>
                    <closer>
                        <signed>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Delcassé</hi>.</signed>
                    </closer>
                </frus:attachment>
            </div>
        </body>
